<p>When I press a key(integer) on my keyboard. It does something like:</p>  <pre><code> gchar *keypressed;  keypressed=gdk_keyval_name (event-&gt;keyval);  printf("The KeyEvent is: %s\n", keypressed); // Till here it is fine     </code></pre>  <p>I get segmentation fault when I do this:</p>  <pre><code>char ch; sprintf(ch, "%s\n", keypressed);    printf("The NewKeyEvent is: %s\n",ch); </code></pre>  <p>I need to <em>convert</em> it as I am going to use the value in a <em>switch case</em>. Without converting it is not possible.</p>